---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ConceptPageHero from '../../components/concepts/ConceptPageHero.astro';
import ConceptPager from '../../components/concepts/ConceptPager.astro';
import { getConcept } from '../../lib/concepts';

const c = getConcept('frequency');
---

<Layout title={`${c.title} | Identity Engineering`}>
	<main class="min-h-screen">
		<ConceptPageHero
			scene={c.scene}
			tag={`${c.tag} · ${c.layerLabel}`}
			title={c.title}
			lede={c.blurb}
			scrollHint={c.scrollHint}
		/>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/55">
				<div class="mb-2 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Definition</div>
				<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white md:text-4xl">
					The dynamic state of the tension continuum.
				</h2>
				<p>
					<strong class="text-white/80">Frequency</strong> is the engineering descriptor of the high-dimensional tension continuum in which identities exist and interact. It describes the spectrum of characteristic oscillation frequencies, damping ratios and resonance conditions that determine how an identity’s internal tension field evolves over time.
				</p>
				<p>
					While Rotation provides gyroscopic self-stability of the Identity Stem, Frequency captures the full dynamic behaviour of the surrounding tension field — how it oscillates, couples with other fields (human or ideational), dissipates or stores energy, and maintains or loses coherence under external forces.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
				<div class="mb-6 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Mechanics</div>
				<ul class="space-y-6 text-lg text-white/55">
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Tension field:</strong> The high-dimensional continuum of internal stress, deflection and energy that an identity is permanently exposed to. It is the actual arena in which Sameness-as-Trajectory, Mass and Rotation unfold.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Frequency spectrum:</strong> The characteristic rates and patterns at which tension oscillates and changes. These frequencies encode how an identity responds to internal conflicts and external perturbations.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Resonance:</strong> Frequency matching between two or more tension fields (identities or idea-clusters). Produces mutual amplification, stronger coupling and energetically favourable co-orbits.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Damping:</strong> The rate at which tension oscillations decay. Controls energy dissipation, prevents destructive resonances and determines modal stability of the identity.
					</li>
					<li class="border-l border-white/15 pl-5">
						<strong class="text-white/80">Regulatory Damping (Governance):</strong> External, high-dimensional damping applied by regulation, institutions or collective agreements. Its purpose is the preservation of identity coherence and the optimisation of its tension modes. In the ideal case it is not arbitrary control but the result of collective intelligence defining the most constructive damping vector or tensor.
					</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-8 text-lg leading-relaxed text-white/55">
				<div class="mb-2 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Energy & Mass</div>
				<p>
					Frequency directly connects to the energy perspective of the framework. Inner free energy is liberated when internal conflicts and tensions are resolved. The efficiency with which this energy can be converted into coherent Mass-building motion depends heavily on the damping characteristics of the tension field.
				</p>
				<p>
					Appropriate damping allows resolved tension to be channelled productively. Excessive or misaligned regulatory damping dissipates useful energy or rigidifies the system (overdamped). Insufficient damping permits chaotic amplification or destructive resonances (underdamped). Optimal regulatory damping supports the identity in turning resolved inner energy into stable, expansive Mass while preserving its recognisable trajectory.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="border-t border-white/10 bg-white/[0.02] px-6 py-24">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
				<div class="mb-6 text-sm uppercase tracking-[4px] text-white/40">Engineering work</div>
				<p class="text-lg text-white/55">
					<strong class="text-white/80">Shape internal Frequency and respond intelligently to external regulatory damping.</strong>
				</p>
				<ul class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-lg text-white/55">
					<li>Increase productive resonance with supportive idea-identities and human relationships.</li>
					<li>Reduce destructive energy loss through well-calibrated internal and external damping.</li>
					<li>Maintain coherent, high causal-entropy modes even when regulatory or relational masses shift.</li>
					<li>Monitor the frequency signature of your own tension field and anticipate how external governance inputs will modulate it.</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</section>

		<ConceptPager id="frequency" />
	</main>
</Layout>
